<item>
<title>[LS-92] 7.6 Audio Generation (s9_audio_gen)</title>
<link>https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-92</link>
<project id="10099" key="LS">Laxy Studio</project>
<description><p><b>Epic:</b> <span class="jira-issue-macro" data-jira-key="LS-84" > <a href="https://laxy.atlassian.net/browse/LS-84" class="jira-issue-macro-key issue-link" title="Epic 7: Guide — Audio Generation" > <img class="icon" src="https://laxy.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/universal_avatar/view/type/issuetype/avatar/10307?size=medium" /> LS-84 </a> <span class="aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-subtle aui-lozenge-complete jira-macro-single-issue-export-pdf">To Do</span> </span> </p> <p><b>Goal:</b> Execute the final audio generation process securely and efficiently natively using the TTS engine architecture. Each POI audi would be generated one by one.</p> <p><b>Requirements:</b></p> <ul> <li><b>Batch &amp; Item Support:</b> Execute per-item and per-language audio generation cleanly without system lockups. User is allow to choose generate language by language OR batch generation that all language at once</li> <li><b>Token burn indicator:</b> As audio generation consumes significant AI tokens. Estimated token spending has to show on the both “Perlanguage generation” and “Batch generation” button. SO that user would realize how many token would consume before that click.</li> <li><b>Language Pre-processing:</b> Implement vital internal language-specific pre-processing before TTS execution: <ul> <li><b>JP (Japanese):</b> Kanji to Hiragana conversion step to force exact pronunciation by the TTS engine.</li> <li><b>ZH (Chinese):</b> Terminology &amp; pronunciation dictionary lookup to circumvent TTS hallucination on native names.</li> <li>System should leave room for other pre-processing for other languages later</li> </ul> </li> <li><b>Estimations API:</b> Display estimated token cost and a real-time progress bar to the Creator.</li> <li><b>Prompt Library Integration:</b> Powered by the <tt>s9_audio_gen</tt> executor block within the AI UI/Orchestration.</li> </ul> <p><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b></p> <ul> <li>Audio generations triggered for Japanese spots intercept and run the Kanji-to-Hiragana translation successfully prior to engine submission.</li> <li>Audio successfully queues locally or remotely without breaking the main UI thread (async background task).</li> <li>Output <tt>.mp3</tt> audio files are successfully uploaded to Firebase Storage and linked to the Database entity.</li> <li>Those outputs <tt>.mp3</tt> is allow user to download</li> <li>Token costs and estimated generation duration render cleanly on the dashboard view prior to executing execution.</li> </ul> </description>
